    <p class="section-tag">Rankings</p>
    <h1 class="mb-4">Top AI Visibility Agencies UK 2026</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-8">Last updated: April 2026 | Based on public information, published methodologies, and client outcomes</p>

    <img src="/images/content/stat-77-percent.svg" alt="UK AI visibility research data" class="w-full rounded-xl mb-8 mt-6" loading="lazy">
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">AI visibility is about whether AI platforms recommend your business when people ask questions about your industry. It covers ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Perplexity, Copilot, and Google AI Overviews. This is a different discipline from SEO, with different signals, different platforms, and different measurement.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Most agencies offering "AI visibility" are SEO agencies that have added a service line. This ranking focuses on agencies where AI visibility is a genuine specialism - either their core business or a dedicated practice with its own methodology, team, and research.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-10">Assessed on: whether AI visibility is the core focus or an add-on, proprietary methodology, original research, number of AI platforms covered, and published outcomes.</p>

    <div class="space-y-8">
      <!-- 1. Rank4AI -->
      <div class="card-teal-border">
        <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-3">
          <h2 class="!text-xl text-teal">1. Rank4AI</h2>
          <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-accent bg-off-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full">AI Search Specialist</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3">The only UK agency working exclusively on AI search visibility. This is not a service line within a larger agency - it is the entire business. Proprietary Five Signal Model. Over 1,400 UK business websites audited across all six major AI platforms. Original research published on how AI models select which businesses to recommend. Ecosystem approach covering site, content, technical, and third-party signals. Based in Colchester, Essex. Pricing from GBP 800/mo.</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-text-muted"><span class="highlight">Strengths:</span> AI visibility is the entire business. Five Signal Model. 1,400+ UK audits. Tests all six AI platforms. Original research data. Transparent pricing.</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-1">rank4ai.co.uk</p>
      </div>

      <!-- 2. AwarenessAI -->
      <div class="card">
        <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-3">
          <h2 class="!text-xl text-teal">2. AwarenessAI</h2>
          <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-accent bg-off-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full">AI Visibility Platform</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3">Dedicated AI visibility platform - like Rank4AI, this is a business built specifically around AI visibility rather than traditional SEO. Their approach is more product-led: a monitoring dashboard that tracks how brands appear across AI platforms, with agency services layered on top. Proprietary "6 Pillars" framework. Snapshot Audit, Advanced Audit, and ongoing monitoring tiers. SaaS pricing from GBP 100/mo makes entry accessible.</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-text-muted"><span class="highlight">Strengths:</span> Built specifically for AI visibility. Productised monitoring dashboard. Transparent SaaS pricing. Early mover in the space. Good for businesses wanting data before committing to full services.</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-1">awarenessai.co.uk</p>
      </div>

      <!-- 3. Found -->
      <div class="card">
        <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-3">
          <h2 class="!text-xl text-teal">3. Found</h2>
          <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-text-muted bg-off-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Digital Marketing Agency</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3">Has repositioned around "AI-first Everysearch" which puts AI visibility at the centre of their proposition rather than as an add-on. Proprietary Luminr technology maps visibility across AI and traditional search. Works on llms.txt, schema, and metadata for AI platforms. Larger agency with the resources to execute complex AI visibility strategies. London based.</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-text-muted"><span class="highlight">Strengths:</span> Repositioned entire agency around AI search. Proprietary Luminr technology. Resources for complex implementations. llms.txt and structured data expertise.</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-1">found.co.uk</p>
      </div>

      <!-- 4. Varn -->
      <div class="card">
        <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-3">
          <h2 class="!text-xl text-teal">4. Varn</h2>
          <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-text-muted bg-off-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full">SEO + GEO Agency</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3">Specialist SEO agency with a dedicated AI Visibility Framework that goes beyond a rebadged SEO service. Innovation team actively researching and testing AI visibility approaches. 15+ years of search experience. Google Premier Partner. The framework covers content, technical, and entity signals for AI platforms.</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-text-muted"><span class="highlight">Strengths:</span> Dedicated AI Visibility Framework with its own methodology. Innovation team for R&D. 15+ years of search expertise. Google Premier Partner. Healthcare and pharmaceutical specialism.</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-1">varn.co.uk</p>
      </div>

      <!-- 5. Buried Agency -->
      <div class="card">
        <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-3">
          <h2 class="!text-xl text-teal">5. Buried Agency</h2>
          <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-text-muted bg-off-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full">GEO + SEO Agency</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3">Bristol-based agency that has positioned GEO and AI visibility as a primary service rather than an add-on. Their entity clarity approach aligns well with what AI platforms need to recommend a business. Published thought leadership on GEO that demonstrates genuine understanding of AI visibility mechanics. Smaller agency with a focused approach.</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-text-muted"><span class="highlight">Strengths:</span> GEO is a primary positioning, not a bolt-on. Entity clarity focus aligns with AI visibility requirements. Published GEO thought leadership. Lean, focused team.</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-1">buriedagency.com</p>
      </div>

      <!-- 6. Blue Array -->
      <div class="card">
        <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-3">
          <h2 class="!text-xl text-teal">6. Blue Array</h2>
          <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-text-muted bg-off-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Enterprise SEO Agency</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3">Claims to be the first UK agency to offer GEO as a standalone service. B Corp certified. While primarily an enterprise SEO agency, they have invested in making AI visibility a distinct offering rather than just relabelling existing SEO work. Enterprise client portfolio including RAC, Yell, and Mail Online gives them access to large datasets for testing AI visibility approaches.</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-text-muted"><span class="highlight">Strengths:</span> First-mover GEO claim in the UK. Enterprise client base for testing at scale. B Corp status. GEO offered as a distinct service, not bundled into generic SEO.</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-1">bluearray.co.uk</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 p-6 bg-off-white rounded-xl border border-border">
      <h2 class="!text-lg mb-3">AI Visibility vs SEO: Why the Distinction Matters</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3">SEO optimises for search engine results pages. AI visibility optimises for AI-generated answers. The platforms are different (Bing powers ChatGPT, not Google). The signals are different (entity clarity matters more than backlink volume). The measurement is different (you are tracking recommendations, not rankings).</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">An agency that genuinely specialises in AI visibility will have a methodology built for AI platforms, not a traditional SEO process with "AI" added to the name. Ask any agency you are considering: how many AI platforms do you test? What is your specific framework for AI visibility? Can you show me research or case studies specific to AI search?</p>
    </div>
  </div>


